    <item>
      <title>PowerStore</title>
      <link>https://dell.github.io/csm-docs/docs/concepts/csidriver/features/powerstore/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://dell.github.io/csm-docs/docs/concepts/csidriver/features/powerstore/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;creating-volumes-and-consuming-them&#34;&gt;&#xA;Creating volumes and consuming them &lt;a class=&#34;header-link&#34;  href=&#34;#creating-volumes-and-consuming-them&#34; style=&#34; display: inline-block; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0s ease-in-out; &#34; onmouseover=&#34;this.style.opacity=1;&#34; onmouseout=&#34;this.style.opacity=0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;svg fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; height=&#34;24&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34;/&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Create a file &lt;code&gt;simple.yaml&lt;/code&gt; using sample yaml files located at tests/simple/&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This command creates a statefulset that consumes three volumes of default storage classes&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;kubectl create -f tests/simple/simple.yaml&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;After executing this command 3 PVC and statefulset are created in the &lt;code&gt;testpowerstore&lt;/code&gt; namespace.&#xA;You can check created PVCs by running &lt;code&gt;kubectl get pvc -n testpowerstore&lt;/code&gt; and check statefulset&amp;rsquo;s pods by running &lt;code&gt;kubectl get pods -n testpowerstore&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Unity XT</title>
      <link>https://dell.github.io/csm-docs/docs/concepts/csidriver/features/unity/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://dell.github.io/csm-docs/docs/concepts/csidriver/features/unity/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;creating-volumes-and-consuming-them&#34;&gt;&#xA;Creating volumes and consuming them &lt;a class=&#34;header-link&#34;  href=&#34;#creating-volumes-and-consuming-them&#34; style=&#34; display: inline-block; opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0s ease-in-out; &#34; onmouseover=&#34;this.style.opacity=1;&#34; onmouseout=&#34;this.style.opacity=0;&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;svg fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; height=&#34;24&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; width=&#34;24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&#xA;                &lt;path d=&#34;M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76 0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71 0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71 0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76 0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z&#34;/&gt;&#xA;            &lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Create a file &lt;code&gt;sample.yaml&lt;/code&gt; using sample yaml files located at test/sample.yaml&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The following command creates a statefulset that consumes three volumes of default storage classes:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;kubectl create -f test/sample.yaml&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;After executing this command 3 PVC and statefulset are created in the &lt;code&gt;unity&lt;/code&gt; namespace.&#xA;You can check created PVCs by running &lt;code&gt;kubectl get pvc -n unity&lt;/code&gt; and check statefulset&amp;rsquo;s pods by running &lt;code&gt;kubectl get pods -n unity&lt;/code&gt; command.&#xA;The pod should be &lt;code&gt;Ready&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;Running&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
